    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Tfj9zlJbMLvA"
      },
      "source": [
        "# 🧠 Problem Statement\n",
        "Design and implement a DL model capable of learning the underlying structure, grammar, and contextual dependencies of a given text corpus to generate coherent and meaningful text sequences using:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Vanilla RNN**\n",
        "2. **LSTM**\n",
        "3. **GRU**\n",
        "\n",
        "Then compare:\n",
        "- training loss\n",
        "- generated text quality\n",
        "- memory handling\n",
        "- long-term dependency learning"
      ],
      "id": "Tfj9zlJbMLvA"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 1,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "zp-eync7MLvB",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "b8398c93-78bf-4d77-d580-b464562b0e7c"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "TensorFlow: 2.20.0\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.text import Tokenizer\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.sequence import pad_sequences\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras import Sequential\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Embedding, SimpleRNN, LSTM, GRU, Dense\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "print(\"TensorFlow:\", tf.__version__)"
      ],
      "id": "zp-eync7MLvB"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6eBYOyFuMLvB"
      },
      "source": [
        "# 📥 Load Text Corpus\n",
        "We use a **small built-in sample corpus** so students can run this quickly.\n",
        "You can later replace it with:\n",
        "- Shakespeare text\n",
        "- song lyrics\n",
        "- chatbot data\n",
        "- story paragraphs\n",
        "- custom PDF extracted text"
      ],
      "id": "6eBYOyFuMLvB"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 2,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9XkSz_7uMLvB",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "6911babb-a4dd-41ac-c6c6-8c804ae3ad18"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "\n",
            "deep learning is transforming artificial intelligence\n",
            "recurrent neural networks are useful for sequential data\n",
            "lstm helps remember long term dependencies\n",
            "gru is faster and simpler than lstm\n",
            "text generation models predict the next word\n",
            "deep learning models can generate meaningful sentences\n",
            "\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "corpus = '''\n",
        "deep learning is transforming artificial intelligence\n",
        "recurrent neural networks are useful for sequential data\n",
        "lstm helps remember long term dependencies\n",
        "gru is faster and simpler than lstm\n",
        "text generation models predict the next word\n",
        "deep learning models can generate meaningful sentences\n",
        "'''\n",
        "print(corpus)"
      ],
      "id": "9XkSz_7uMLvB"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8FGYDhWWMLvC"
      },
      "source": [
        "# 🔤 Tokenization & Sequence Creation\n",
        "We convert text into integer tokens and create **n-gram style sequences**\n",
        "for next-word prediction."
      ],
      "id": "8FGYDhWWMLvC"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 4,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "eGdrXNS1MLvC",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "80ca046c-123f-419d-acd1-e6d88ab0d9bb"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Vocabulary size: 37\n",
            "X shape: (35, 7)\n",
            "y shape: (35,)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "tokenizer = Tokenizer()\n",
        "tokenizer.fit_on_texts([corpus])\n",
        "\n",
        "total_words = len(tokenizer.word_index) + 1\n",
        "print(\"Vocabulary size:\", total_words)\n",
        "\n",
        "input_sequences = []\n",
        "for line in corpus.split('\\n'):\n",
        "    token_list = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences([line])[0]\n",
        "    for i in range(1, len(token_list)):\n",
        "        n_gram_seq = token_list[:i+1]\n",
        "        input_sequences.append(n_gram_seq)\n",
        "\n",
        "max_len = max(len(seq) for seq in input_sequences)\n",
        "input_sequences = pad_sequences(input_sequences, maxlen=max_len, padding='pre')\n",
        "\n",
        "X = input_sequences[:, :-1]\n",
        "y = input_sequences[:, -1]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"X shape:\", X.shape)\n",
        "print(\"y shape:\", y.shape)"
      ],
      "id": "eGdrXNS1MLvC"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xWUFTySuMLvC"
      },
      "source": [
        "# 🧠 Model 1: Vanilla RNN\n",
        "This is the baseline sequential model.\n",
        "It struggles with long-term dependencies because of vanishing gradients."
      ],
      "id": "xWUFTySuMLvC"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 5,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yFwqVOV7MLvC",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "62235adc-c898-4c71-f31e-80c975013f13"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stderr",
          "text": [
            "/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/keras/src/layers/core/embedding.py:100: UserWarning: Argument `input_length` is deprecated. Just remove it.\n",
            "  warnings.warn(\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Vanilla RNN training completed\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "rnn_model = Sequential([\n",
        "    Embedding(total_words, 64, input_length=max_len-1),\n",
        "    SimpleRNN(128),\n",
        "    Dense(total_words, activation='softmax')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "rnn_model.compile(loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n",
        "                  optimizer='adam',\n",
        "                  metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
        "\n",
        "rnn_history = rnn_model.fit(X, y, epochs=200, verbose=0)\n",
        "print(\"Vanilla RNN training completed\")"
      ],
      "id": "yFwqVOV7MLvC"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "m3qr9wTbMLvC"
      },
      "source": [
        "# 🔒 Model 2: LSTM\n",
        "LSTM uses **input, forget, and output gates**\n",
        "to preserve long-term memory."
      ],
      "id": "m3qr9wTbMLvC"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 9,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DdVsEJAzMLvC",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
